passages.text: Reiterate Rating: NEUTRAL | PO: 29.00 CNY | Price: 24.18 CNY

TGOOD reported 2Q25 financial results on 27 August. Revenue in 2Q25 was RMB4.2bn, up \(25\%\) YoY, \(2\%\) above our expectation. Its GPM came in at \(27.4\%\) , up 2.8ppt YoY/5.3ppt QoQ, above our estimate of \(25.1\%\) , thanks to the profitability improvement of both its electrical equipment and EV charging network business. Operating income (clean EBIT) was RMB450mn, up \(53\%\) YoY, \(17\%\) above our forecast. Net income in 2Q25 was RMB262mn, up \(99\%\) YoY, in line with its preliminary result range (RMB225- 283mn, \(+71\% - 115\%\) YoY) and \(6\%\) above our forecast. Its NPM in 2Q25 was \(6.7\%\) , \(+2.7\) ppt YoY/4.5ppt QoQ, in line with our estimate.

In 1H25, revenue from its electrical equipment (i.e. smart manufacturing + integrated services segment) grew \(20\%\) YoY to RMB4.4bn, supported by the solid growth of grid investment and renewable energy capacity addition. Revenue from EV charging network grew \(9\%\) YoY to RMB1.8bn. TELD (TGOOD's EV charging infrastructure subsidiary) recorded a net loss of RMB4mn in 1H25, narrowing YoY from RMB25mn in 1H24. Its GPM also improved 0.9ppt YoY to \(30.3\%\) . As of end- 1H25, TELD had 792k units of public charging piles in operation, including over 470k units of DC chargers. In 1H25, TELD achieved a total charging volume of 8.6TWh (up \(47\%\) YoY).

Factoring in TGOOD's 2Q25 results, we lift our 2025/26/27E earnings forecast by \(3\% /4\% /2\%\) on higher sales forecast of electrical equipment and higher GPM estimates. As such, we raise our PO to RMB29 (from RMB28), based on a 20x average 2025/26E P/E (unchanged) for its electrical equipment business and 2.0x average 2025/26E P/S (unchanged) for its EV charging network business. We reiterate Neutral rating on its somewhat fair valuation and likely slowdown in its renewable energy-related orders in 2H25- 2026E.

Electrical Equipment

Qingdao TGOOD Electric Co., Ltd. is the largest charging network operator in China with \(20\%\) market share in public charging piles in operation by 2024. The company also supplies electrical equipment (gas insulated switchgear, mid-voltage switchgear, transformer) and prefabricated substations used in renewable power generation, power grid, industrial and energy system.

We have a Neutral rating for TGOOD. We favor the earnings growth prospects of its EV charging network business driven by the uptrend of EV charging infrastructure in 2025- 30, as well as improving profitability thanks to rising equipment utilization. That said, we think the normalizing wind & solar capacity addition in China will weigh on the revenue growth of its electrical equipment business in 2025- 26E. TGOOD's current valuation looks rich compared with its domestic peers.

We derive our PO of RMB29 using the SOTP method. We value its traditional electrical equipment business with 20x average 2025/26E P/E, line with the average of its domestic peers due to similar growth. We apply 2.0x average 2025/26E P/S for its EV charging network business (TELD).

Upside risks: (1) higher-than- expected EV penetration, (2) faster- than- expected growth of charging infrastructure utilization, (3) stronger- than- expected growth of wind/solar capacity addition in China
Downside risks: (1) slowdown of EV sales in China, (2) intensifying competition in charging network, (3) slowdown of renewable energy development in China, (4) competition from battery swap
